Summary: As a user, I want to share files with my course-mates using Dropbox
Creator: Abhishek Maiti
Description:
I want to create notes in the Notebook section to make rough gist of the course studies.

Steps:

# Login to the eLearning portal
# Go to my courses
# Click on the subscribed course
# Scroll down and click on Dropbox

Acceptance Criteria:

Users should be able to share files with their fellow batchmates by uploading.

There should be a file creation option to store multiple files in a folder.

The file category name field should accept alphabets, numbers, special characters. It is a mandatory field.

On the dropbox homepage, sent and received files should be present.

There must be an option to apply bulk changes to all the sent or received files.

Summary: As a user, I want to use the Notebook for saving my notes
Creator: Abhishek Maiti
Description:
I want to create notes in the Notebook section to make rough gist of the course studies.

Steps:

# Login to the eLearning portal
# Go to my courses
# Click on the subscribed course
# Scroll down and click on Notebook

Acceptance Criteria:

The Note title field should contain alphabets, numbers, special characters. The maximum limit is 30 characters. It is a mandatory field.

The Note details field should contain alphabets, numbers, special characters. There is no maximum limit for characters. It is not a mandatory field. Users should be able to change the text colour, font, size etc. 

There should be a Back button to undo any unintended note creation.

On the notebook homepage, all notes should be present.

There should be options to sort all the notes according to date of creation, modification and alphabetically in ascending or descending order.
